1
00:00:01,030 --> 00:00:02,290
Greetings everyone.

2
00:00:02,570 --> 00:00:11,830
In this video clip our talk will be about homemade machine for winding multi-turn coils, of Tesla transformer type.

3
00:00:12,550 --> 00:00:17,990
All who ever wound them know what laborious process this is and how much time it takes.

4
00:00:18,710 --> 00:00:31,690
For example, wind such Tesla on 50-mm frame by time, where work takes about hour of intensive labor.

5
00:00:32,170 --> 00:00:38,610
Make it in manual mode quite simple, because such diameter easily fits in hand.

6
00:00:39,170 --> 00:00:55,390
But when speech goes about winding such coils, here frame diameter 153 millimeters, and besides if it's covered with varnish, then in manual mode do this already very problematic.

7
00:00:56,370 --> 00:01:02,690
Made I such construction in couple of evenings, considering that glue dried.

8
00:01:04,210 --> 00:01:16,810
Machine itself made from solid pine, width 20 centimeters and length from front rack of machine to end of lower guide makes 80 centimeters.

9
00:01:16,810 --> 00:01:31,930
Front rack of machine fastened rigidly, and rear rack has possibility to move along lower guide, thereby can install here frames of different lengths.

10
00:01:31,930 --> 00:01:50,110
Here from central hole to base of lower guide 16 centimeters, which can allow us to install coil about 30 centimeters in diameter for winding wire.

11
00:01:52,510 --> 00:02:00,340
Work on this construction should start with that could find some motor with reducer.

12
00:02:00,950 --> 00:02:07,510
In this case in my stocks I found such, can't say from what, sometime bought it incidentally.

13
00:02:08,370 --> 00:02:19,430
Main moment here is gear ratio, here it makes 100 to 1, that is 100 motor revolutions correspond to 1 revolution of central shaft.

14
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:29,890
Motor here DC and this very good, since can further here make rotation regulation.

15
00:02:30,330 --> 00:02:35,110
Minimum tool set for this construction is jigsaw.

16
00:02:36,550 --> 00:02:49,610
Advise to apply on jigsaw for cutting such small-tooth blades, they very well suit for cutting plywood, but also end cut turns out quite quality.

17
00:02:50,670 --> 00:02:58,110
Further this is screwdriver, set of bits and some set of drills.

18
00:02:58,670 --> 00:03:01,350
Carpenter's glue and bit of patience.

19
00:03:03,550 --> 00:03:08,210
Front rack for us glued at angle 90 degrees.

20
00:03:08,970 --> 00:03:16,790
Desirable to follow this angle, so we didn't have further beatings and curvatures of central guide rotation axis.

21
00:03:17,870 --> 00:03:26,770
Rear rack installed on lower guide also at angle 90 degrees at its movement.

22
00:03:26,770 --> 00:03:34,730
Well and here visible that I here traced lines, that here also we have angle 90 degrees.

23
00:03:38,430 --> 00:03:45,930
By rear rack it's also glued, but glued it to this point.

24
00:03:47,130 --> 00:03:49,990
Here have adjustment screws.

25
00:03:50,870 --> 00:03:56,010
Width of rear rack of machine, I slightly planed it.

26
00:03:56,010 --> 00:04:00,510
Thereby it's 3 millimeters narrower than main guide.

27
00:04:01,830 --> 00:04:06,490
And here visible certain gaps from one side and other.

28
00:04:07,170 --> 00:04:23,870
These gaps allow me with tightening of these screws to set support force on lower guide so that this rear rack could move with effort and didn't pop out.

29
00:04:23,870 --> 00:04:29,490
Fastened it then to lower guide at these holes with screws.

30
00:04:32,690 --> 00:04:38,370
This part seated on carpenter's glue, as and these guide corners.

31
00:04:39,570 --> 00:04:46,530
Central rotation axis of coil is 6 millimeter stud with cut thread.

32
00:04:46,530 --> 00:04:54,130
Cut thread along its whole length allows easily to choose needed distance for installing guide disks.

33
00:04:54,730 --> 00:05:00,910
Guide disks also cut from solid plywood thickness 9 millimeters.

34
00:05:01,430 --> 00:05:06,570
After disk cut, drew I it with compass.

35
00:05:07,190 --> 00:05:12,630
All put on axis, axis clamped in screwdriver and rotates.

36
00:05:12,630 --> 00:05:20,010
Edges passed with sandpaper help, thereby acquired clear geometric circle.

37
00:05:21,290 --> 00:05:33,510
And with sandpaper we fit these disks under moment that they with effort enter tube of frame of future Tesla coil.

38
00:05:35,130 --> 00:05:37,210
So construction works in assembly.

39
00:05:38,410 --> 00:05:49,810
Now revolution number doing regulation with lab power supply help by changing supply DC potential.

40
00:06:06,320 --> 00:06:10,020
Now move to some small tricks.

41
00:06:10,280 --> 00:06:15,800
At end I'll show how on this machine wound Tesla transformer.

42
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:26,000
Before start of winding wire cut frame of necessary length, according to calculation of winding length on this frame.

43
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:30,140
And make hole through which will pass wire.

44
00:06:30,320 --> 00:06:32,080
This will be start of winding.

45
00:06:32,200 --> 00:06:35,060
I made it at this point with awl help.

46
00:06:36,060 --> 00:06:43,780
After hole made, its top cleaned with knife help, so was even surface.

47
00:06:45,860 --> 00:06:59,160
Recommend to do start hole couple centimeters from edge of frame, so then was distance for which could conveniently fix coil on board.

48
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:09,740
And now when hole made, can move to installation of guide disk.

49
00:07:10,620 --> 00:07:13,180
Front guide disk I already fastened.

50
00:07:13,180 --> 00:07:17,640
And rear guide disk is in movable position.

51
00:07:18,440 --> 00:07:26,800
Rear guide disk will install so this hole that was made was in front.

52
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:34,560
After guide disks tightened, coil frame put on its place.

53
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:49,800
Front guide disk put practically at edge of coil frame, and rear precisely sunk on depth so hole for wire in frame was behind it.

54
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:53,380
Can demonstrate.

55
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:57,500
Awl enters, and here is tip.

56
00:07:57,580 --> 00:07:59,200
Here will pull through wire.

57
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:02,300
Remained two unfastened nuts.

58
00:08:02,420 --> 00:08:07,160
This will do support in rear part of machine rack.

59
00:08:08,700 --> 00:08:14,880
Now here moment stud that's rotation axis and has through hole.

60
00:08:15,460 --> 00:08:24,200
Same through hole present at transitional shaft made from copper tube of corresponding diameter.

61
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:42,580
At putting this shaft on stud, hole becomes coaxial and in hole lowered cotter pin, thereby preventing rotation of coupling on stud.

62
00:08:42,580 --> 00:08:55,640
Stud from this side round, and from opposite end I made forming under reducer shaft.

63
00:08:57,060 --> 00:09:01,120
All made from plywood 9 mm.

64
00:09:01,520 --> 00:09:11,340
Here glued magnet that serves as revolution sensor on machine.

65
00:09:11,340 --> 00:09:14,040
It activates reed switch.

66
00:09:14,800 --> 00:09:23,280
Now I installed guide axis between front support rack of machine and rear.

67
00:09:23,380 --> 00:09:37,400
Rear support rack movable, it can move along machine guide board, thereby we can change installation point under various frame lengths.

68
00:09:37,400 --> 00:09:43,440
I approximately made myself winding machine for coils length 80 cm.

69
00:09:43,660 --> 00:09:45,840
This quite enough for my needs.

70
00:09:46,540 --> 00:09:56,420
Also on stud I installed spacer tube that abuts this point.

71
00:09:57,300 --> 00:10:07,080
So wood didn't break from thread, I made washer, seating it on two screws.

72
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:17,480
Precisely into it abuts copper spacer tube and already it then abuts these spacer nuts.

73
00:10:18,140 --> 00:10:25,580
Important to accurately strengthen whole construction so it didn't have play.

74
00:10:25,580 --> 00:10:31,680
Because when will wind wire, if there'll be play, this will reflect additional inconveniences.

75
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:36,080
And so when pressed, system works stably.

76
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:46,180
Construction of rear support of machine fastened to guide with two screws.

77
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:51,260
In front and rear part and analogously from opposite side.

78
00:10:51,260 --> 00:10:59,860
Thereby construction acquires rigidity and can be in all positions installed.

79
00:11:00,940 --> 00:11:05,040
Here I removed play with nuts help.

80
00:11:06,060 --> 00:11:09,360
Now axial shift absent.

81
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:13,800
Can pay attention how reed switch works.

82
00:11:17,820 --> 00:11:22,380
When magnet approaches, reed switch contact attracts.

83
00:11:22,380 --> 00:11:26,000
And closes system.

84
00:11:28,140 --> 00:11:39,520
Output of reed switch through this adapter will be connected to calculator.

85
00:11:40,060 --> 00:11:42,540
It'll count revolutions.

86
00:11:43,540 --> 00:11:46,920
I did connection of calculator to reed switch.

87
00:11:46,920 --> 00:11:54,720
These two conductors going into calculator, now connected on board parallel to contacts of equals key.

88
00:11:55,420 --> 00:11:57,200
How this works?

89
00:11:57,360 --> 00:12:03,200
Turn on calculator and dial so it counted revolution count for us.

90
00:12:03,580 --> 00:12:09,540
1 plus 1 and press equals.

91
00:12:12,360 --> 00:12:16,240
Calculator now switched to Grand Total mode.

92
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:24,340
And at each press of equals key, it'll add last addend to previous number.

93
00:12:24,440 --> 00:12:26,060
Last addend was 1.

94
00:12:26,380 --> 00:12:32,060
Thereby, we now at each press will sum plus 1.

95
00:12:33,540 --> 00:12:38,680
Now turn on system, apply power.

96
00:12:45,870 --> 00:12:56,890
And see that at shaft rotation our calculator counts revolution count.

97
00:13:05,460 --> 00:13:16,420
If supply voltage increase, revolutions accelerate and count goes faster.

98
00:13:18,700 --> 00:13:22,200
There's one more feature of using calculator.

99
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:30,720
For example, winding we and our wire sharply went on overlap and we passed some turn count.

100
00:13:30,720 --> 00:13:34,300
And system continues count for us.

101
00:13:35,280 --> 00:13:45,080
Turn off power and remember number of revolutions that was on calculator.

102
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:46,500
Now we have 46.

103
00:13:46,760 --> 00:13:48,100
Zero indicator.

104
00:13:49,660 --> 00:13:51,140
Now enter it again.

105
00:13:51,380 --> 00:13:52,140
46.

106
00:13:53,260 --> 00:13:54,360
Minus.

107
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:58,040
And dial one.

108
00:14:03,040 --> 00:14:09,440
Now unwind turn count manually back to spool that went on overlap.

109
00:14:10,340 --> 00:14:14,780
And calculator at that subtracts turn count.

110
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:17,280
I now rotate in manual mode.

111
00:14:17,380 --> 00:14:18,200
45.

112
00:14:19,460 --> 00:14:20,500
Unwind.

113
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:22,500
44.

114
00:14:26,230 --> 00:14:32,830
Thus we unwind defect that happened during winding.

115
00:14:36,490 --> 00:14:44,830
And further don't forget at subsequent start of winding to switch system again to summing mode.

116
00:14:45,470 --> 00:14:46,850
Repeat same operation.

117
00:14:46,990 --> 00:14:48,190
Our 40 turns.

118
00:14:48,790 --> 00:14:51,270
Add one.

119
00:14:52,070 --> 00:14:59,010
And at subsequent system start calculator will count in larger direction.

120
00:15:01,210 --> 00:15:11,310
This important moment that we count turn count that coil frame did for us.

121
00:15:11,370 --> 00:15:17,850
To precisely know quantity of meters of wire that was laid on this frame.

122
00:15:17,850 --> 00:15:22,430
This in moment to us will be useful then at frequency fitting.

123
00:15:22,510 --> 00:15:26,850
Combining frequency of LC resonance with frequency of wave on conductor length.

124
00:15:27,130 --> 00:15:36,650
Important addition to construction of this machine serves frame on which will rotate spool with winding wire.

125
00:15:37,510 --> 00:15:44,530
This simplest variant, made on quick hand, but nevertheless from this its effectiveness doesn't decrease.

126
00:15:44,530 --> 00:15:56,750
Sense in setting spool so its lower cheeks rubbed against lower surface of board.

127
00:15:57,190 --> 00:16:01,910
Thereby because of friction force we provide certain wire tension.

128
00:16:02,990 --> 00:16:04,570
Here it slips.

129
00:16:05,470 --> 00:16:11,910
Visible places where spool frame rubs during rotation.

130
00:16:12,910 --> 00:16:31,070
If this moment not provided, then will be very hard at winding wire to hold so turns didn't go off, because will need constantly use second hand as tensioning mechanism.

131
00:16:31,490 --> 00:16:35,410
And at such reception process much simplifies.

132
00:16:35,410 --> 00:16:43,730
In best case, of course, here on construction provide some additional friction, adjustable, but this in future.

133
00:16:44,450 --> 00:16:50,750
For now for winding couple coils such variant quite working.

134
00:16:51,410 --> 00:16:57,790
Here made holes under plastic guide at certain needed me height.

135
00:16:58,830 --> 00:17:03,370
And whole this system quite well showed itself in work.

136
00:17:03,370 --> 00:17:10,790
Before start of winding coil frame dry-wiped if there any contamination on surface.

137
00:17:11,110 --> 00:17:17,570
Then leads wire into frame hole and bends in opposite side to winding direction.

138
00:17:18,630 --> 00:17:22,810
Fixed conductor from inside of frame with sticky tape help.

139
00:17:23,780 --> 00:17:26,330
I fixed it in two places.

140
00:17:28,490 --> 00:17:33,350
Visible that it's fixed.

141
00:17:34,350 --> 00:17:36,650
Now can move to winding.

142
00:17:36,970 --> 00:17:43,530
First meters will be hardest, until form about tens of turns.

143
00:17:43,750 --> 00:17:50,730
Further motor rotation speed can increase and systematically wind.

144
00:17:51,730 --> 00:17:54,430
Spool with wire installed on floor.

145
00:17:55,310 --> 00:18:03,550
Machine itself install at edge of table and do first wire revolutions manually on frame.

146
00:18:04,290 --> 00:18:08,450
At that don't forget to turn on calculator for revolution count.

147
00:18:08,910 --> 00:18:10,650
Thus this happens.

148
00:18:17,720 --> 00:18:24,120
Necessary to do about 4-5 turns.

149
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:27,360
Pay attention that I dropped wire.

150
00:18:27,360 --> 00:18:30,900
Nothing unwinds since wire has certain tension.

151
00:18:31,620 --> 00:18:38,640
Now shift wire carefully along coil axis.

152
00:18:39,680 --> 00:18:43,200
Form perpendicular direction to frame.

153
00:18:43,860 --> 00:18:49,640
This most complex part of start of winding work.

154
00:18:53,660 --> 00:18:56,660
Carefully do this work.

155
00:18:58,480 --> 00:19:02,580
And further all will go much faster.

156
00:19:03,960 --> 00:19:06,720
Correct start of wire done.

157
00:19:07,420 --> 00:19:10,060
Calculator counted already 11 turns.

158
00:19:10,220 --> 00:19:15,880
And now at subsequent winding conductor lays evenly.

159
00:19:16,880 --> 00:19:22,320
Now can already move to winding mode in automatic mode.

160
00:19:24,800 --> 00:19:27,740
Order of automatic winding so.

161
00:19:28,900 --> 00:19:33,300
With nail of index finger of left hand I hold turns.

162
00:19:34,340 --> 00:19:37,520
And right hand slightly lead conductor.

163
00:19:38,180 --> 00:19:42,220
Thereby do laying turn to turn.

164
00:19:42,220 --> 00:19:44,320
Now I apply power.

165
00:19:44,780 --> 00:19:47,440
First small potential.

166
00:19:47,540 --> 00:19:49,600
Motor here at 24 volts.

167
00:19:49,980 --> 00:19:51,460
Apply about 9 volts.

168
00:19:52,060 --> 00:19:54,340
And then can accelerate rotation.

169
00:19:58,640 --> 00:20:00,720
Rotation slowly started.

170
00:20:01,720 --> 00:20:03,200
I hold.

171
00:20:05,240 --> 00:20:08,820
And increase supply voltage.

172
00:20:18,680 --> 00:20:24,980
In such mode happens winding.

173
00:20:27,160 --> 00:20:34,680
As do about 50 turns, speed can increase.

174
00:20:39,620 --> 00:20:40,420
Rotation.

175
00:20:42,620 --> 00:20:45,880
Because already appears rigidity of start.

176
00:20:51,420 --> 00:20:54,680
I applied 20 volts of power.

177
00:21:00,530 --> 00:21:03,810
Now calculator already shows 60 turns.

178
00:21:04,970 --> 00:21:06,230
We managed to lay.

179
00:21:13,730 --> 00:21:17,130
As they say, primitively but effectively.

180
00:21:44,280 --> 00:21:51,660
Now I laid 100 turns on coil frame.

181
00:21:53,700 --> 00:21:56,040
Such came out winding for us.

182
00:21:57,560 --> 00:22:01,100
First turn we then carefully equalize.

183
00:22:02,480 --> 00:22:05,360
Calculator shows exactly 100 turns.

184
00:22:05,760 --> 00:22:07,640
What now I recommend to do?

185
00:22:09,100 --> 00:22:10,460
Very important moment.

186
00:22:10,660 --> 00:22:14,300
Because in winding process can happen different things.

187
00:22:15,220 --> 00:22:19,200
Will go on overlap wire or something else.

188
00:22:19,880 --> 00:22:25,200
Every 100 turns make mark on frame behind conductor.

189
00:22:25,380 --> 00:22:26,800
And mark turn count.

190
00:22:27,340 --> 00:22:36,540
Thereby if something happened for you, you always can unwind conductor back to coil spool.

191
00:22:36,800 --> 00:22:40,940
Reach point of turn count that indicated for you here.

192
00:22:41,620 --> 00:22:47,340
And further go from precise count point.

193
00:22:47,340 --> 00:22:51,240
Now I'll apply this marker mark.

194
00:22:59,340 --> 00:23:00,260
Like this.

195
00:23:01,140 --> 00:23:03,500
And sign.

196
00:23:04,740 --> 00:23:08,100
Here at this point we had 100 turns.

197
00:23:08,700 --> 00:23:11,400
What calculator shows us.

198
00:23:12,520 --> 00:23:13,590
Work finished.

199
00:23:14,080 --> 00:23:19,220
Took somewhere 15 minutes for whole this coil winding operation.

200
00:23:19,320 --> 00:23:22,120
Turn count recorded here.

201
00:23:23,220 --> 00:23:25,820
By readings 832 turns.

202
00:23:26,760 --> 00:23:30,300
And edge of wire fixed with sticky tape help.

203
00:23:30,480 --> 00:23:33,500
Plus additionally 2 turns made.

204
00:23:33,920 --> 00:23:40,060
Now can move to painting coil with first layer of shellac.

205
00:23:40,800 --> 00:23:42,400
It'll fix whole wire.

206
00:23:42,900 --> 00:23:46,180
Won't give it further to wind off, go away.

207
00:23:46,280 --> 00:23:49,480
Especially this critical for coil edges.

208
00:23:51,820 --> 00:23:54,580
Varnishing too one pleasure.

209
00:23:54,700 --> 00:23:59,480
DC motor and voltage regulation.

210
00:24:00,560 --> 00:24:02,780
I can regulate revolution count.

211
00:24:02,940 --> 00:24:07,920
Of course also to this machine will need to make foot pedal.

212
00:24:08,420 --> 00:24:14,240
Which will work as PWM regulator in system.

213
00:24:14,920 --> 00:24:17,780
And then will be absolute convenience.

214
00:24:18,590 --> 00:24:25,720
Before start of varnishing coil passed with napkin help.

215
00:24:25,820 --> 00:24:26,760
Remove dust.

216
00:24:30,280 --> 00:24:35,020
And now can directly apply varnish.

217
00:24:35,100 --> 00:24:37,080
Apply will with small brush.

218
00:24:38,880 --> 00:24:39,680
Dip in varnish.

219
00:24:39,680 --> 00:24:40,400
Here.

220
00:24:41,900 --> 00:24:48,580
And with such simple movement varnish applied.

221
00:24:48,800 --> 00:24:52,440
That is not need even apply efforts.

222
00:24:53,160 --> 00:24:56,020
Varnish evenly distributes by turns.

223
00:25:08,340 --> 00:25:12,160
Small such mechanization pleasant and convenient.

224
00:25:13,360 --> 00:25:19,740
Small coils of smaller diameters can of course wind manually.

225
00:25:19,740 --> 00:25:26,060
But such, with diameter 150 mm, this already extremely inconvenient.

226
00:25:26,720 --> 00:25:28,760
And thin wire will be very long.

227
00:25:31,620 --> 00:25:44,120
Also at such method of applying varnish, after whole coil covered, leave it at slow rotation for 20 minutes.

228
00:25:44,760 --> 00:25:51,420
And thereby very evenly varnish distributes without drops.

229
00:25:53,720 --> 00:25:54,760
Convenient.

230
00:26:00,900 --> 00:26:04,300
In whole so covered whole coil.

231
00:26:07,500 --> 00:26:08,060
Here.

232
00:26:08,640 --> 00:26:10,520
One coil I already made.

233
00:26:12,560 --> 00:26:13,600
Covered with varnish.

234
00:26:15,640 --> 00:26:18,000
Here it second same.

235
00:26:22,160 --> 00:26:23,660
Covered with one layer.

236
00:26:23,780 --> 00:26:29,520
Fully identical to that one I now wound.

237
00:26:36,650 --> 00:26:38,330
On this all.

238
00:26:40,090 --> 00:26:41,090
Assemble.

239
00:26:41,390 --> 00:26:43,630
Construction not complex.

240
00:26:44,430 --> 00:26:50,750
For work on its making me in light tempo took 2 days.

241
00:26:52,330 --> 00:26:53,290
Everyone luck.
